summary:
The Security Council,

Guided by the UN Charter, recalled relevant mandates and resolutions. Reaffirming resolution 2282 and General Assembly resolution 70/262, it noted efforts and progress made. Welcoming Secretary-General's consultations on reform proposals, it took note of ongoing work.

The Council welcomed the Secretary-General's report on Peacebuilding and Sustaining Peace, taking note of recommendations and options. It:

1. Decides to discuss the report's recommendations further;
2. Notes General Assembly's invitation to UN bodies to explore implementation of report's recommendations during its 72nd and 73rd sessions;
3. Notes General Assembly's request for an interim report from Secretary-General during its 73rd session on recommendations, including financing for peacebuilding activities;
4. Notes General Assembly's request for a detailed report during its 74th session on implementation of resolution 70/262 and report's recommendations.

5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
